Each of these phases may last several years.
 The first one is the riskiest for the investor, because the success of
 the enterprise isn't yet established.
 The second phase is the safest, and also where the most money is made,
 because the company is growing simply by duplicating its successful formula.
 The third phase is the most problematic, because the company runs into
 its limitations.
