Projected performance
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Sales and Earnings.
 Try to look for companies that are expected to grow by double digits.
 Be stricter as company size gets smaller because smaller companies should
 be growing faster than large ones.
 Large - at least 10% a year, medium at least 15% and small companies at
 least 20%.
 Value Line has this number for example.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Projected Stock High/Low.
 Analysts spend their lives trying to be accurate and it never hurts to
 see what they expect to happen.
 Both the high and low price projections must be bigger than the current
 price.
 Never invest in a stock that's expected to fall in price.
 Also, make sure the low projection represents a worthwhile gain.
 Value Line prints this price.
\end_layout

